# Review Writer Pipeline â€” Implementation Plan

## Goal
Create `core/review_writer.py` module that wires all review prompts into an executable pipeline.

## Proposed Changes

### [NEW] [review_writer.py](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/review_writer.py)

New module with 7 functions following existing [rewriter.py](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py) patterns:

| Function | Prompt | Input | Output |
|----------|--------|-------|--------|
| [extract_blueprint()](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#969-1010) | [system_extract_blueprint.txt](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/system_extract_blueprint.txt) | script text | blueprint dict |
| `recommend_framework()` | [system_recommend_framework.txt](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/system_recommend_framework.txt) | blueprint + frameworks list | rankings dict |
| `check_blueprint()` | [system_check_blueprint.txt](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/system_check_blueprint.txt) | blueprint + framework eval_focus | completeness report |
| `convert_units()` | None (pure Python) | blueprint + target_country | converted blueprint |
| `create_outline()` | [system_review_outline.txt](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/system_review_outline.txt) | blueprint + framework + style_guide | outline dict |
| `write_review_chapter()` | [system_write_from_blueprint.txt](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/system_write_from_blueprint.txt) | blueprint + outline chapter + context | chapter text |
| `verify_facts()` | [system_verify_facts.txt](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/system_verify_facts.txt) | written text + blueprint + target_country | verification report |

**Patterns from rewriter.py:**
- [_load_prompt(name, lang)](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#154-167) â€” reuse existing
- `api_client.call_api(messages, temperature, timeout)` â€” standard signature
- `log_callback(msg)` â€” for UI feedback
- JSON response parsing via `re.search(r'\{[\s\S]*\}', content)`
- `stop_check` â€” interruptible API calls

**Unit conversion (`convert_units`):**
- Pure Python, no API call
- Traverses `product_evaluation` array in blueprint
- Converts weight (kgâ†”lbs), length (mm/cmâ†”inches), distance (mâ†”yards), price (EURâ†”USD)
- Only US and EU targets

## Verification Plan

### Manual Test
1. Run the app
2. Load a gun review script
3. Test [extract_blueprint()](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#969-1010) â€” check product_evaluation has structured data
4. Test `recommend_framework()` â€” check all 8 frameworks scored
5. Test `convert_units()` â€” check units match target country
6. Test full pipeline end-to-end

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This module creates the functions only. UI integration (buttons, callbacks) will be a separate step.
